    "Author": "Fair Seat Purchase",
    "DateCreated": "2025-01-01",
    "DateLastModified": "2025-01-01",
    "Description": "Single-table DynamoDB data model for the Fair Seat Purchase challenge. One table 'FairSeatPurchase' holds both SEAT and TXN entities, distinguished by key prefixes and the Entity_Type attribute. GSI1 (sparse) serves the available-seat map / per-section count; GSI2 (sparse, write-sharded) serves the expired-hold sweep. TTL attribute Hold_Expiration (epoch seconds) is registered for passive/auxiliary cleanup ONLY and is NOT the seat-release mechanism; seat release relies on condition-at-read-time plus an optional GSI2 sweeper (see DESIGN.md). AttributeType 'S' = string, 'N' = number. Sample data includes >=5 representative items per table and per index: >=6 available seats (populate GSI1), >=5 held seats (populate GSI2), 2 sold seats, and 4 purchase transactions across pending/paid+confirmed/failed states.",
    "AWSService": "Amazon DynamoDB",
    "Version": "3.0"
  },
